	<exercise><statement><p> Why does an object weigh a different amount when in air and when submerged in water? </p></statement></exercise>
	<exercise><statement><p> If the string was cut on your first object (while submerged), what would be the acceleration of the object? </p></statement></exercise>
	<exercise><statement><p> Why is it important to make certain that no air bubbles adhere to the object during the submerged weighing procedures? </p></statement></exercise>
