	<exercise><statement><p> When calculating <m>Q_a</m>, does one of the terms, <m>\Delta T_a</m>, <m>m_a</m>, or <m>c_a</m>, have a significantly larger relative uncertainty?  If so, what is it about that measurement that made that uncertainty large while the others were small?  Is this uncertainty improvable? </p></statement></exercise>
